description:
Crack the speed barrier wide open in this thrilling new adventure that redefines what it means to go full throttle!

As the final leg of the Super Bonk Rally fast approaches, Shine and her crew must come to grips with the shocking reality of her past! And, even more perilous than the skeletons in her closet are the dangers of her present-as the racers attempt to put an end to her success-once and for all!

Told in a series of five legs within the race of all races-the Super Bonk Rally, this five issue mini-series will span amazing landscapes and death-defying terrain, as these racers go completely Psycho Bonkers!

name: The Pilot

description:
When Toulon's Puppets were freed to live in the flesh once more they expected to find their happy endings. Unfortunately, death continues to follow them... but this time they are on the wrong side of the wooden bodies.

Both the tension and body count rise as "THE REBIRTH" continues!

description: In the year 3499, programmed UNION Soldier 034 infiltrates the Separatist City of Subterra in search of the Psion Machine, humanity's most sought-after and cryptic super technology. The mission falls apart when he finds that he and the infamous machine share a puzzling bond.

The Shield-Brethren are a secret martial order that has defended the West for centuries. Now, the origins of the order are revealed in this three-issue graphic novel collection.

As the soldiers of Greece return from war with Persia, they are greeted not as heroes but merely as more mouths to feed. Athens is overflowing with the poor and desperate. For some of the former soldiers, this life is not why they fought. They crave adventure. They need money. More than anything, though, they long for purpose.

Our heroes, seeking to realize the idea offered to them by the philosopher Plato, leave Athens and travel to Delphi with hope of visiting the oracle. They have a dream to found a city of their own, and they desire insight from the oracle as to their question. But their skills—both as warriors and as thinking men—will be tested by adversaries they do not even know they have.

This comic contains explicit content and is recommended for mature readers.
name: GN

description: Jack Kurtzberg is a successful writer of witch romance bestsellers... and he hates it so much. Suffering from writer's block after the death of his brother, he decides to move back to his hometown, not knowing that his new neighbors are a coven of beautiful, blood-thirsty, demon-worshipping witches hiding in plain sight. This volume reprints the critically acclaimed horror miniseries written by El Torres.
name: TPB

description: Jerry von Lind has a fondness for "old-school", as is evident by the use of his actual family title "Baron". A long-time commercial artist , Jerry's real love is illustrating the ladies, as you’ll soon discover in this amazing collection! One of our absolute favorites!
name: Pin-up Perfection

volume.name: The Art of Baron von Lind

description: Jerry 'Baron' Von Lind knows how to create pin-up art that's as bewitching and alluring as anything created in the last century! This all-new gallery celebrate's the Baron's need for luscious ladies in lingerie and naughty smiles on beautiful faces!
name: Volume 2

volume.name: The Art of Baron von Lind

description: Back from the undead - it's a return to the series that started it all! Now the body count is up to SIX, with a new collection of little vampire vixens poised to rip out your throat and look good doing it! This latest showcase of pretty plasma junkies has art Pelaez, Le Blanc, Cuevas, Enric, Giorello and many more. Cover painting by Joe Jusko.

description: In the neverending battle between good and evil, not even death is permanent. The Shaman, a mysterious mage with a trick permanently up his sleeve and the ability to restore life, has tasked himself with raising those on both sides of the battle from the grave. Working alongside a foulmouthed teenage sorceress and a retired superhero bored with the life in tights, the Shaman and his adoptive family fight monsters, demons, and even the odd astronaut or two, if that's what gets the job done!
name: Vol. 1

description: From the team behind the international phenomenon Logicomix comes a new graphic novel, Democracy, written and illustrated by Alecos Papadatos and in collaboration with Abraham Kawa. Democracy opens in 490 BCE, when Athens is at war. Leander, trying to rouse his comrades for battle, begins to recount his own life, bearing direct witness to the evils of the old tyrannical regimes and to the birth of a new political system. The story that emerges, of the death of the gods and the tortuous birth of democracy, is crammed with extraordinary characters and tells in incident and vivid detail how this greatest of civic inventions came about. We see that democracy was born through a combination of chance and historical contingency - but also through the cunning, courage, and willful action of a group of highly talented and driven individuals.
name: GN

description: From classics like "The Tortoise and the Hare" and "The Grasshopper and the Ants" to obscure gems like "The Frogs Who Desired a King," Fable Comics has something to offer every reader. Twenty-eight fables from different cultures and traditions are wonderfully adapted and illustrated in comics format by twenty-six different cartoonists. Edited by New York Times-bestselling Fairy Tale Comics' Chris Duffy, this jacketed hardcover is a beautiful gift and an instant classic.
name: HC

description: The Esu are in full attendance as they return in a Counsel of Monsters! And Rathraq is humbled by a new foe. New for him, anyway.

The ghosts of Ragnarok descend on the crew. Waterson's past is revealed.

description: It's Crime Prevention Week, and Peter Parker, a.k.a. the Ultimate Spider-Man, is in the mood to do a little crime preventing! Luckily, Crime-Master and his goons, the Enforcers, are here to help!

A mysterious character who goes by the name of "Celsia" kidnaps the senator! But seeing that Celsia can not only melt bullets with her hands in an instant, but also freeze the lasso of truth, Wonder Woman needs to figure out how to save the senator from the wrath of Celsia's hands-and quick! Celsia 451 part 2 of 3: "The Fire Within"
name: Celsia 451 Part 2 of 3: The Fire Within

description: The children and the town residents are working towards conflicting ends, a fact which soon becomes apparent to John Sr. along with other faults in his operation. The town prepares for lock-down while Jim alternately attempts to reason with the residents and escape. Where Jim fails, the children seemingly succeed.
name: Chapter Five: Trio

description: One night, in an isolated observatory, an astronomerreceives a binary-code signal from space— not only the apparent proof of the existence of extra-terrestrial intelligence, but a signal that contains the solution to one of the biggest mathematical enigmas, the sequens of prime numbers. When the astronomer and the message mysteriously disappear, a real international intrigue begins, involving Martin Mystère and Java, ufologists, industriali spies and Men in Black. And they all want to seize a secret that can change the future of the world.
name: Il Paradosso di Fermi

description: An uncanny reality appears during the shooting of a TV show in Africa: there lives a tribe of terrifyingly ruthless humanoids. Their physical appearance suggests they were born and raised in the darkness, far away from the sun light and warmth. Where do they come from? What’s their origin? Martin Mystère is one of the few who know the truth: he met those people before, and he knows they’re not monsters. It’s the beginning of an investigation that will bring the Detective of the Impossible on a long path, looking for traces of the creatures “born in the dark”…
name: Gli Abitatori del Sottosuolo

description: A short cruise on the Pacific waters becomes a terrifying nightmare that brings back to light long-forgotten horrors. In the depths of the ocean, a creature with huge, deadly tentacles waited for decades before waking up again: it’s the kraken, the biblical Leviathan, whose name is whispered in terror by the sailors and whose nature is now known only by a few people. While the world is puzzling over this horror, only an old Native American, a veteran of WWII, can solve the enigma; that’s why he asks Martin Mystère for help. Cooperating with a young oceanologist, the Detective of the Impossible ventures into the sea abyss, in search of a secret coveted by obscure forces...
name: Protocollo Leviathan

description: A forceful eartquake strikes in Sri Lanka. A secret hidden in the entrails of the Earth. A mad scientist who tried to destroy the world. A movie with the images of the end of New York City. A lethal new kind of bomb. A kid called “Bat Boy”. A deadly videogame. A 10-billion dollar blackmailing. And, looming over all this, the huge metal shadow of what in the past had been called “The Allagalla Terror”. The Detective of the Impossible and a group of unlikely allies are faced with the consequences of a diabolical invention created 50 years ago!
name: La Minaccia di Allagalla

description: This is a combination of issues 26/27

Martin Mystère is in a clinic, in a catatonic condition, and he doesn’t react to any stimulus. His brilliant and inquisitive mind appears to be utterly lifeless, cut off from the world, and the doctors have no hope for a recovery. Diana and Java are distraught, but don’t give up on him and continue to visit Martin, looking for something that could spark his interest for the world once again. All their efforts are useless, though. What happened to the Detective of the Impossible? What plunged him in that condition? The answer is to be found in Switzerland, on the day that should have marked a turnaround in the life of his former enemy Sergej Orloff. A day when the past forcefully resurfaced, instead, and a tragedy happened. The fateful day of Orloff’s wedding!
name: Il Matrimonio di Sergej Orloff

description: Martin Mystère refuses to go to the Antarctic with the strange Dr. Jonathan Ziegler; when the scientist reaches the South Pole on his own, he dies dramatically. The Detective of the Impossible is plagued by his guilty feelings for having declined to help Ziegler, and at the same time he’s worried because he literally feels “split in two”, just like he’s living another life along his own, a life where he took different decisions. To solve this disquieting riddle, Martin chooses to go to the place where Ziegler met his end, in a place he never saw before and at the same time feels he’d already visited: Longitude Zero!
name: Ritorno a Longitudine Zero

description: South-eastern Iran. The Moon becomes as bright as the sun; Jiroft’s archaeological site is invaded by thousands of adders; other inexplicable phenomena shock the area. New York. After the announcement of her discovery of Aratta, the legendary Sumerian city-state, young archaeologist Margot Jordan-Shair is the victim of an attempted kidnapping; her mysterious attackers die, melting like wax statues. It’s the beginning of a journey that will take Martin Mystère to the land of the Sumer, where somebody is awakening from a millenary sleep, determined to seize back power and bring chaos to the Earth.
name: Il Risveglio di Tiamat

description: Join the Teen Scene Investigators as they explore some of Riverdale's greatest mysteries in this digital-only collection! Archie and the gang have joined forces with a couple of professional forensic investigators and are solving crimes one clue at a time. Can they close these cases before it's too late?
It's a race against the clock as Batman burns rubber to reach the Calendar Man and rescue a kidnapped newborn child!
name: Burning the Days Part 4 of 4

description:
Batman Day is here! Celebrate the Dark Knight with BATMAN: ENDGAME SPECIAL EDITION #1! In this special edition issue, the Joker returns to Gotham City with a new mindset. After years of playing games, he's finally going to do what he's danced around for years. He's going to kill Batman. And he's going to do it using those who Batman loves the most: the Justice League.

This special edition comic features the first chapter to BATMAN VOL. 7: ENDGAME—the biggest, boldest story that the #1 New York Times best-selling creative team of Scott Snyder and Greg Capullo have told to date—as well as an exclusive, all-original 8-page prologue to BATMAN AND ROBIN ETERNAL #1 from the mind of Scott Snyder!

Note: Many characters appear only on covers, which themselves are mostly reprints of earlier covers

name: Combat Part 1 of 9

description: In October 2015, DC Entertainment's creator-driven imprint, Vertigo, is set to release 12 new #1s, over 12 consecutive weeks, that push the boundaries of genre fiction-horror, fantasy, crime thriller and sci-fi. This preview book gives you a first look at the projects included in this groundbreaking rollout including THE TWILIGHT CHILDREN by Gilbert Hernandez and Darwyn Cooke, LUCIFER by Holly Black and Lee Garbett and UNFOLLOW by Rob Williams and Mike Dowling. Don't miss this opportunity to check out all of these new titles from Vertigo veterans and a powerhouse of new voices and rising art stars.

France, december 1789. The power of King Louis XVI is declining fast; the Bastille fell, the revolutionaries are triumphing. In great secret, the King starts a plan to save his riches, transporting it to England. The priceless cargo of gold and jewelry is loaded on the “Telemaco”, that sails along the Seine to reach the English Channel. On September 3, 1790, after reaching the Quillebeuf Bay, the ship sinks, and the wreck hasn’t been found until now. Or was it? That’s what the Detective of the Impossible has to find out about, in an engrossing “treasure hunt”.
name: Il Naufragio del Telemaco

description: New York is shaken by a savage double murder: a man has been bitten on his throat, maybe by a wild beast, while a woman’s heart appears to have been seized by an invisible hand that crushed it until it blew up. A model is shocked by the news: she happens to know a man capable of doing something like that—her great-grandfather, a feared and powerful shaman. The girl asks Martin Mystère for help, and the Detective of the Impossible finds himself facing a mystery centered around a society of highly regarded characters, who are mutually bound by an old pact.
name: I predatori della Foresta Sacra

description: He was known as Za-Te-Nay, or "The Man with the Hatchet", the lead character of a series of dime novels, published during the XIX century, and his name was shrouded in legend! The Detective of the Impossible has learned that he was no fictional character, but he was real and his destiny was bonded with something that happened on a distant planet, a long time ago. After many years, the hero's weapon, an hatchet that possesses extraordinary powers, is at the center of some mysterious happenings with which Martin Mystère, Java and a small artifact of unknown origins, seemingly gifted with its own will, are involved...
name: L'ombra di Za-Te-Nay
